  "notes": [
    "Schedule SE (Form 1040) AcroForm widget map for the IRS-hosted TY2025 PDF (PDF /Title metadata: '2025 Schedule SE (Form 1040)').",
    "TY2024-vs-TY2025 deltas: none observed for the line layout. Schedule SE has not had substantive line changes since the 2020 restructure that combined the long/short forms. The SS wage base on line 7 increases yearly (TY2025: $176,100; SSA 2024-10-10 press release).",
    "Page 1 carries Part I (lines 1a-13) \u2014 the taxpayer-facing SE tax calculation. Layer 1 ScheduleSEFields covers all 22 line widgets on page 1.",
    "Page 2 (Part II \u2014 optional methods, lines 14-17) is left in unmapped_widgets. Most filers never elect optional methods; modeling them is a follow-up.",
    "Layer 1 always writes ZERO to lines 1a, 1b, 4b, 5a, 5b, 8b, 8c (deferred features: farm income, CRP payments, optional methods, church employee income, Form 4137 tips, Form 8919 wages). The widgets are mapped so the renderer writes a 0 \u2014 same convention as Form 1040 widgets that Layer 1 has a value for but always 0.",
    "Line 7 (SS wage base) is a CONSTANT for TY2025 ($176,100). Layer 1 writes the constant. Future years require updating SS_WAGE_BASE_TY2025 in skill/scripts/output/schedule_se.py."
  ],
